The paper proposes a new clustering technique that is fully automatic and can detect arbitrarily shaped clusters. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning, artificial intelligence, computer vision, and data mining. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are likely sub-categories given the focus on developing a new clustering technique. Additionally, cs.DM (Data Mining) is a likely sub-category given the use of edge length statistics in the MST of the dataset. Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible sub-category given the potential application of the proposed clustering technique in analyzing social networks.
